台灣大學寫作教學中心-工程學術英文寫作與口頭報告















工程學術英文寫作與口頭報告Academic Writing and Presentation in Engineering Studies


This course intends to train students to critically read and write academic journal research papers in engineering studies. Students will also be trained how to make an oral presentation of their research. 
To achieve the course objectives, the training includes introductions to English academic writing and presentation and to the framework of each part of an engineering academic paper. Each training session consists of two hours of lectures/class discussions and one hour group discussions/writing tasks. While the two-hour-lectures/class discussions equip students with the essential fundamental knowledge of writing English engineering papers, the one-hour-group-discussions enable students to practice the knowledge and skills using authentic publications in engineering field. A variety of learning tasks (guided reading/writing practices, class/paired discussions, and individual/ collaborative writing tasks) are designed at an attempt to develop students’ writing skills and better understanding of the structural features of research papers relevant to engineering studies. By the end of the training, students should finish an individual term paper or a collaborative writing project, making use of the moves and techniques learned from the course. In addition, students are provided the opportunity to apply their trained presentation techniques to conduct their simulation poster presentation and oral presentation.
課程大綱







